on making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nAll have some interpersonal deficits. Which candidate balances strengths best? B handles stress well, conscientious, good weather assessment (critical), computer skills (modern avionics). Communication tone issues but maybe mitigated? C quick decisions, attention, altruistic (good for crew), but not willing to further education (bad for long-term). A strong anticipation and spatial vision (important for navigation), leadership, but unfriendly and unhealthy (health matters for long flights). D strong problem solving, responsibility, concentration, but moody, loner, weak leadership.\n\nProbably B is best overall: stress handling, conscientiousness, technical weather assessment, computer skills. Interpersonal issues but maybe less severe than others? A's unfriendly and unhealthy could affect long flights. C's lack of education willingness is concerning for long-term. D's moody and loner may affect crew.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate B.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing reasoning and ask if any other agents have info on candidate strengths we lack, maybe about teamwork for any candidate."}
